  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow">Product knowledge</p>
    <h1>Tape Measure Accuracy Classes Explained for B2B Buyers</h1>
    <p>Accuracy is one of the most important product details for tape measure buyers. The right accuracy level depends on the target market, product positioning, and user expectations.</p>
    <h2>Why accuracy class matters</h2>
    <p>Accuracy class helps buyers understand how closely a tape measure follows measurement standards over a defined length. For retail and professional users, accuracy can affect trust in the product and brand.</p>
    <h2>What buyers should confirm</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Target accuracy class or market requirement</li>
      <li>Tape length and printing scale</li>
      <li>Inspection method used before shipment</li>
      <li>Packaging claims and label wording</li>
      <li>Whether certificates or test records are required</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>How WOOKTOOL can support RFQs</h2>
    <p>When buyers share their target market, product grade, and packaging requirements, WOOKTOOL can help review which tape measure specification is suitable for quotation and sampling.</p>
  </article>
  <CTA title="Need help specifying tape measure accuracy?" primaryLabel="Contact Sales Team" />
</BaseLayout>
